{"rendered": {"description": {"raw": "Actually, this branch doesn't remove any boost.  However, it does a bunch of cleanup and fixes to lay the groundwork for my next PR, which will remove the last part of boost::filesystem.\r\n\r\n* Use the Filesystem.cc built-in separator function.\r\n\r\n    That way, we don't have duplicate code in Filesystem_TEST.cc\r\n\r\n* Add in tests for links.\r\n\r\n* Make sure create_and_switch_to_temp_dir succeeds.\r\n\r\n* Switch to using the ASCII versions of the Windows functions.\r\n\r\n    This allows us to get rid of the funky widen and narrow functions.\r\n\r\n* Make sure to include array and string in converter.cc\r\n\r\n    It uses them both.\r\n\r\n* Combine Windows implementations of exists and is_directory.\r\n\r\n    They are almost the same anyway.\r\n\r\n* Combine implementations of separator() function.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Actually, this branch doesn't remove any boost.  However, it does a bunch of cleanup and fixes to lay the groundwork for my next PR, which will remove the last part of boost::filesystem.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Use the Filesystem.cc built-in separator function.</p>\n<p>That way, we don't have duplicate code in Filesystem_TEST.cc</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Add in tests for links.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Make sure create_and_switch_to_temp_dir succeeds.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Switch to using the ASCII versions of the Windows functions.</p>\n<p>This allows us to get rid of the funky widen and narrow functions.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Make sure to include array and string in converter.cc</p>\n<p>It uses them both.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Combine Windows implementations of exists and is_directory.</p>\n<p>They are almost the same anyway.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Combine implementations of separator() function.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>", "type": "rendered"}, "title": {"raw": "Remove boost 15", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Remove boost 15</p>", "type": "rendered"}}, "type": "pullrequest", "description": "Actually, this 